    "In study [69], they also relied on a set of extracted features from user and textual features.",
    "To extract the textual features, they used both classic word embedding (word2vec, fastText, and Keras embedding layer) and context-based embedding (Multilingual Arabic Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (MARBERT) and ARBERT) with deep learning models [70].",
    "Two deep learning schemes were used: Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (BiLSTM).",
    "The result showed that MARBERT with CNN provided the best accuracy of 95.6%.",
    "Alawadh et al. [71] performed another experiment using machine learning algorithms and Mini-BERT."
